#!/usr/bin/env bash
set -euo pipefail

repo_root="$(cd "$(dirname "${BASH_SOURCE[0]}")/.." && pwd)"
public_repo="${KERNEL_PUBLIC_REPO:-/Users/enzo/projects/Home Lab/cubie-a7s-armbian}"

cat <<CHECKLIST
# A733 Patch Prep Checklist

Run these gates after the corrected-root runtime proof passes and before
creating any maintainer-facing branch, patch export, cover letter, or mail.

1. Exact v4 Cubie runtime proof:

   cd ${repo_root} && scripts/cubie-latest-corrected-root-proof --strict

2. Maintainer-ready workflow gate:

   cd ${repo_root} && scripts/kernel-workflow-status --maintainer-ready-strict

3. A733 series shape gate on the public export:

   cd ${repo_root} && scripts/a733-series-shape-gate "${public_repo}/patches"

4. Public hygiene gate:

   cd ${repo_root} && scripts/kernel-public-hygiene-gate "${public_repo}"

5. Backup posture:

   cd ${repo_root} && scripts/kernel-workflow-status --workflow-backup-status

The current 9-patch scaffolding export is not sendable. A future sendable
candidate must be the narrow DTS/board slice, carry the two active Depends-on
IDs for the A733 CCU and pinctrl RFCs, avoid vendor U-Boot workaround state in
DTS, and avoid Ethernet, VPU, display, wireless, USB-C, PCIe, and other feature
creep.
CHECKLIST
